<div style="width: 52px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Unbalanced_scales.svg" class="image" title="Unbalanced scales.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/fe/Unbalanced_scales.svg/45px-Unbalanced_scales.svg.png" width="45" height="40" border="0" /></a></div>
</td>
<td class="mbox-text" style="">The <b><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Neutral_point_of_view" title="Wikipedia:Neutral point of view">neutrality</a> of this article is <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NPOV_dispute" title="Wikipedia:NPOV dispute">disputed</a></b>. Please see the discussion on the <a href="/wiki/Talk:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution" title="Talk:Second Amendment to the United States Constitution">talk page</a>. Please do not remove this message until the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NPOVD#What_is_an_NPOV_dispute.3F" title="Wikipedia:NPOVD" class="mw-redirect">dispute is resolved.</a> <small><i>(January 2009)</i></small></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The <b>Second Amendment</b> (Amendment II) to the <a href="/wiki/United_States_Constitution" title="United States Constitution">United States Constitution</a> is the part of the <a href="/wiki/United_States_Bill_of_Rights" title="United States Bill of Rights">United States Bill of Rights</a> that protects a right to keep and bear arms. The meaning and scope of this right has been described as among the most contested of the rights codified in the Bill of Rights.<br clear="all" /></p>
<table class="infobox" style="text-align: center; font-size:90%;" width="200px">
