<li id="cite_note-46"><b><a href="#cite_ref-46" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Garry_Wills" title="Garry Wills">Wills, Garry</a>. <i>To Keep and Bear Arms</i>. New York Review Of Books, September 21, 1995.</li>
<li id="cite_note-isbn0-300-09562-7-47"><b><a href="#cite_ref-isbn0-300-09562-7_47-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWilliams.2C_David_H.2003">Williams, David H. (2003). <i>The mythic meanings of the Second Amendment: taming political violence in a constitutional republic</i>. New Haven, Conn: Yale University Press. pp.&#160;5. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0300095627" class="internal">ISBN 0-300-09562-7</a>.  "The amendment thus guarantees a right to arms only within the context of a militia, not an individual right to arms for self-defense or hunting."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+mythic+meanings+of+the+Second+Amendment%3A+taming+political+violence+in+a+constitutional+republic&amp;rft.aulast=Williams%2C+David+H.&amp;rft.au=Williams%2C+David+H.&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B5&amp;rft.place=New+Haven%2C+Conn&amp;rft.pub=Yale+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-300-09562-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Cramer-Olson001-48">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Cramer-Olson001_48-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Cramer-Olson001_48-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFCramer.2C_Clayton_E..3B_Olson.2C_Joseph2008">Cramer, Clayton E.; Olson, Joseph (2008). "What Did "Bear Arms" Mean in the Second Amendment?". <i>Georgetown Journal of Law &amp; Public Policy</i> <b>6</b> (2).</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=What+Did+%22Bear+Arms%22+Mean+in+the+Second+Amendment%3F&amp;rft.jtitle=Georgetown+Journal+of+Law+%26+Public+Policy&amp;rft.aulast=Cramer%2C+Clayton+E.%3B+Olson%2C+Joseph&amp;rft.au=Cramer%2C+Clayton+E.%3B+Olson%2C+Joseph&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.volume=6&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
