<li id="cite_note-121"><b><a href="#cite_ref-121" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLund">Lund, Nelson. "Heller and Second Amendment Precedent". <i>Lewis &amp; Clark Law Review, Forthcoming</i>.  "...neither the court below nor the defendants offered the Supreme Court any reasons in support of the challenged judgment, and the Justices heard arguments only from the government.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Heller+and+Second+Amendment+Precedent&amp;rft.jtitle=Lewis+%26+Clark+Law+Review%2C+Forthcoming&amp;rft.aulast=Lund&amp;rft.aufirst=Nelson&amp;rft.au=Lund%2C+Nelson&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-122"><b><a href="#cite_ref-122" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/scripts/getcase.pl?navby=CASE&amp;court=US&amp;vol=307&amp;page=175" class="external text" title="http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/scripts/getcase.pl?navby=CASE&amp;court=US&amp;vol=307&amp;page=175" rel="nofollow">"U.S. Supreme Court United States v. Miller, 307 U.S. 174, 175 (1939)"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/scripts/getcase.pl?navby=CASE&amp;court=US&amp;vol=307&amp;page=175" class="external free" title="http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/scripts/getcase.pl?navby=CASE&amp;court=US&amp;vol=307&amp;page=175" rel="nofollow">http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/scripts/getcase.pl?navby=CASE&amp;court=US&amp;vol=307&amp;page=175</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-01-05</span>.  ""No appearance for appellees.""</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=U.S.+Supreme+Court+United+States+v.+Miller%2C+307+U.S.+174%2C+175+%281939%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcaselaw.lp.findlaw.com%2Fscripts%2Fgetcase.pl%3Fnavby%3DCASE%26court%3DUS%26vol%3D307%26page%3D175&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
