<li id="cite_note-127"><b><a href="#cite_ref-127" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFHoward_J._Fezell">Howard J. Fezell. <a href="http://www.secondamendment.net/2amd4.html" class="external text" title="http://www.secondamendment.net/2amd4.html" rel="nofollow">"The misconstruction of United States v. Miller"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.secondamendment.net/2amd4.html" class="external free" title="http://www.secondamendment.net/2amd4.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.secondamendment.net/2amd4.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-01-05</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+misconstruction+of+United+States+v.+Miller&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Howard+J.+Fezell&amp;rft.au=Howard+J.+Fezell&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.secondamendment.net%2F2amd4.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-128"><b><a href="#cite_ref-128" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFMcClurg1999">[<a href="http://law.fiu.edu/faculty/faculty_mcclurg.htm" class="external text" title="http://law.fiu.edu/faculty/faculty_mcclurg.htm" rel="nofollow">|McClurg, Andrew J.</a>] (1999). ""Lotts" More Guns and Other Fallacies Infecting the Gun Control Debate". <i>Journal of Firearms &amp; Public Policy</i> <b>11</b>: 139.  "But when all is said and done, the only certainty about Miller is that it failed to give either side a clear-cut victory. Most modern scholars recognize this fact. For example, Professor Eugene Volokh describes Miller as “deliciously and usefully ambiguous” in an article about using the Second Amendment as a teaching tool in constitutional law. That is probably the most accurate statement that can be made about the case.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%22Lotts%22+More+Guns+and+Other+Fallacies+Infecting+the+Gun+Control+Debate&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Firearms+%26+Public+Policy&amp;rft.aulast=McClurg&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrew+J.&amp;rft.au=McClurg%2C+Andrew+J.&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.volume=11&amp;rft.pages=139&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
