<li id="cite_note-144"><b><a href="#cite_ref-144" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFWeisselberg.2C_Charles_D.2009">Weisselberg, Charles D. (2009). "<a href="http://aja.ncsc.dni.us/courtrv/cr44-3/CR44-3Weisselberg.pdf" class="external text" title="http://aja.ncsc.dni.us/courtrv/cr44-3/CR44-3Weisselberg.pdf" rel="nofollow">Selected Criminal Law Cases in the Supreme Court's 2007-2008 Term, and a Look Ahead</a>". <i>Court Review</i> <b>44</b>: pp. 99-100.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%5Bhttp%3A%2F%2Faja.ncsc.dni.us%2Fcourtrv%2Fcr44-3%2FCR44-3Weisselberg.pdf+Selected+Criminal+Law+Cases+in+the+Supreme+Court%27s+2007-2008+Term%2C+and+a+Look+Ahead%5D&amp;rft.jtitle=Court+Review&amp;rft.aulast=Weisselberg%2C+Charles+D.&amp;rft.au=Weisselberg%2C+Charles+D.&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.volume=44&amp;rft.pages=pp.+99-100&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
